text: Ursula Braun-Moser (25 May 1937 â€“ 2 May 2022) was a German politician. She was a member of the Christian Democratic Union of Germany, Alternative for Germany, and later the Liberal Conservative Reformers. She was in the European Parliament from 1984 to 1989 and again from 1990 to 1994. She was born in Frankfurt, Germany. Braun-Moser died in Bad Vilbel, Germany on 2 May 2022 at the age of 84. ==References== Category:1937 births Category:2022 deaths Category:MEPs for Germany Category:Politicians from Frankfurt Category:Politicians of the Alternative for Germany Category:Politicians of the Christian Democratic Union of Germany
